This is a great story about a young man who, with his friends makes fun of others who they don't consider "cool".  Then while drinking they are in a car accident and seriously injure a girl from their school who is hoping for a tennis scholarship.  This is a story of how the young man turns his life around.  It's a great watch!

In the genre of LDS films, this was a disappointment. It failed to take the incredible story of Alma into a believable modern context. The acting was quite amateur as well. That said, my young kids (10 and 13) like it. I just have to leave the room when they watch it.
this I purchased for my teens. It was only "okay." It was slow, not one we would watch much. It wasn't realistic to a teens life today, my teenagers could not relate. A one watcher...
My kids ages 7 to 15 all really liked this movie--enough to ask to see it again.
